        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              We've been a small enough that users can just email IT problems. There's only two of us today, but the workforce has grown and getting emailed issues just doesn't cut it. We're about 100 users. I'm looking for a ticketing system that at the very least runs in the browser (IE8, 9, 10). That's pretty much my only real requirement. The only ticketing system I've used is <a href="http://trac.edgewall.org/" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">TRAC</a>, but that seems to be more for software development rather than just general IT issues. I suppose I could use it, but I want to know what else you guys use for a small userbase.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
