              <div class="quotetitle">chalex wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I have worked with many a ticketing system.  With 100 users and 2 responders, they are all overkill and will slow you down.  You should just use a shared mailbox or something.<br /><br />Here's what I use now: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://inboxharmony.com/">http://inboxharmony.com/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />My other favorite one, with 5-10 responders, would be <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://roundup.sourceforge.net/">http://roundup.sourceforge.net/</a><!-- m -->  But it requires configuration.<br /><br />For 10+ responders and many projects, maybe RT?</div><br /><br />I disagree. I'd use a ticketing system if I was the only responder. This is bad advice. If the ticketing system is slowing you down it isn't set up right, or people are bypassing the process, or something else is wrong.

              

              
              
