              <div class="quotetitle">duffbeer703 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Check out ServiceNow (might be too enterprisy) or helpspot.<br /></div><br />ServiceNow is pretty much unusable out of the box. It's easy to make changes, but I wouldn't recommend it for a small shop. Maybe at 15-20 IT users it might become worth the setup time.<br />It feels more like a development environment than prepackaged software. You can change anything with a couple clicks (when you're in as an administrator), for better or for worse.<br /><br />Don't expect to get it going without an engagement with a ServiceNow partner, and training.

              

              
              
